International:
   All Nippon Airways' Acquisition
ANA said the purchase is part of a program to strengthen
its market position in Southeast Asia. The stake will make
ANA one of the six largest shareholders of Abacus, with its
ownership equal to that of Cathay Pacific Airways, China
Airlines, Malaysian Airline Systems, Royal Brunei Airlines
and Singapore Airlines.
   In the U.S., Abacus is affiliated with the Worldspan
Global Travel Information Services computer reservation
system.